Problem:
class HealthMonitor {
  private int calories;
  private boolean exercise;
  private boolean medicate;

  public HealthMonitor(int initialCalories) {
    calories = initialCalories;
    exercise = false;
    medicate = false;
  }

  public void consumeCalories(int amount) {
    calories += amount;
  }

  public void performExercise() {
    exercise = true;
    if (calories > 1500) {
      calories -= 500;
    }
  }

  public void takeMedication() {
    medicate = true;
    calories -= 300;
  }

  public String healthStatus() {
    if (exercise && !medicate && calories < 1800) {
      return "Healthy";
    } else if (!exercise && medicate) {
      return "Under treatment";
    } else if (calories > 2000) {
      return "Unhealthy diet";
    } else {
      return "Status quo";
    }
  }
}",

If medication is administered before evaluating the health status and we observe 'Status quo', can it be concluded that the medication has no effect on health status?
